COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 31, L.D. 67
1 C. The private office of a physician or dentist in individual or group practice.'
2 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
3 'Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §2053, sub-§3-A, as amended by PL 2007, c. 72, §1, is further
4 amended to read:
5 3-A. Health care facility. "Health care facility" means a nursing home that is, or will
6 be upon completion, licensed under chapter 405; a residential care facility that is, or will
7 be upon completion, licensed under chapter 1663; a continuing care retirement community
8 that is, or will be upon completion, licensed under Title 24‑A, chapter 73; an assisted living
9 facility that is, or will be upon completion, licensed under chapter 1664; a hospital; a
10 community mental health facility; a scene response air ambulance licensed under Title 32,
11 chapter 2‑B and the rules adopted thereunder; a facility of a hospice program that is, or will
12 be upon completion, licensed under chapter 1681; a nonprofit statewide health information
13 network incorporated in the State for the purpose of exchanging health care information
14 among licensed health care providers in the State; or a community health center; or an
15 urgent care facility licensed under section 1812-M.'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment clarifies that the licensing standards established in the bill do not
2200 apply to facilities that have a physician, physician assistant or nurse practitioner on site to
2211 provide patient care. It also adds urgent care facilities to the definition of "health care
2222 facility" under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, chapter 413, the laws governing the
2233 Maine Health and Higher Educational Facilities Authority.
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
